 Scottish surname, which is probably derived from the Old Norse personal name <i>Liulfr</i>, composed of an unexplained first element + Old Norse <i>úlfr</i> ‘wolf’.  See also  Lyle ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":11,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":20,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":55,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Vyell Vyvyan was born in 1204, in Cornwall, England, his father, Ralph Vivian, was 30 and his mother, Isabella de Bodrugan, was 27. He had at least 2 sons and 3 daughters with Margaret FitzGerald of Kildare. He died in 1268, in Cornwall, England, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1204–1268":"1204–1268","1228–Male":"1228–Surnud","1230–1273":"1230–1273","1232–1325":"1232–1325","1247–Female":"1247–Surnud","1248–1344":"1248–1344","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1230":"1230","1175":"1175","1273":"1273","ABT 1228":"umbes 1228","1228":"1228","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","12